sentences.english: Julie acts like a love-sick puppy when she's around Mike.
sentences.chinese: 朱莉在迈克身边时，就像是个得了相思病的小狗。

sentences.english: Have you ever seen a one -legged dog making its way down the street?
sentences.chinese: 你可曾见过一只在街上默默行走的的独脚小狗？

sentences.english: The old lady fusses over her little dog as if it were a sick child.
sentences.chinese: 老妇人照顾她的小狗，犹如照顾她生病的孩子。

sentences.english: I drove home with the dog on the front seat beside me.
sentences.chinese: 我开车带小狗回家，它就坐在我旁边的位置上。

sentences.english: He said Ms. Choi became upset when she found the dog alone at his home.
sentences.chinese: 他说崔顺实发现小狗独自待在他家以后变得很生气。

sentences.english: Tana was just a puppy when doctors noticed she had testicles.
sentences.chinese: 当医生发现Tana长了睾丸时，她还只是只小狗。

sentences.english: In the evening, the crestfallen little dog walked by a big tree.
sentences.chinese: 在晚上，小狗垂头丧气的在大树前乱动。

sentences.english: That inspector inspected the kennels and the puppies in it .
sentences.chinese: 检查员检查了狗窝和里面的小狗。

sentences.english: I awoke when my brother threw the dog to my bed.
sentences.chinese: 我弟弟把小狗扔到我床上时我醒了。

sentences.english: Attach the ribbon and note to the collar of the cat or dog.
sentences.chinese: 把绳子和便签挂在小猫或者小狗的脖子上。

sentences.english: A great dog scorns the snarling of a little dog .
sentences.chinese: 一只大狗瞧不起一只小狗的咆哮。

sentences.english: My dog is my perfect companion.
sentences.chinese: 我的可卡是只欢快的小狗。

sentences.english: The outreach team agreed to look after his dog until he returned.
sentences.chinese: 外展小组同意照看他的小狗，直到他出来。
还有小狗巴迪，小猫可可。

sentences.english: Reprimanding your puppy will not stop him from biting.
sentences.chinese: 谴责你的小狗，会不会停止他的咬噬。

sentences.english: Zergling adrenal gland upgrade effects corrected.
sentences.chinese: 小狗肾上腺素的升级效果被修正了。
